cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the modeling and optimization of time-varying data communication networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the optimization of network topology and routing approach, which can be related to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the use of centrality measures, which can be related to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the avoidance of traffic congestion, which can be related to the sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
